CRYPTOGRAPHY
│
├── Key Exchange
│   │
│   ├── Diffie-Hellman (DH)
│   │   └── Agrees on a shared secret over an insecure network
│   │
│   └── Elliptic-Curve DH (ECDH)
│       └── Faster, modern variant of Diffie-Hellman
│
├── Encryption (Confidentiality)
│   │
│   ├── Symmetric Encryption
│   │   │
│   │   ├── AES
│   │   │   └── Encrypts bulk data using a shared secret key
│   │   │
│   │   └── ChaCha20
│   │       └── Stream cipher optimized for software performance
│   │
│   └── Asymmetric Encryption
│       │
│       └── RSA
│           └── Encrypts small data or keys using public/private keys
│
├── Hashing (Integrity)
│   │
│   ├── MD5
│   │   └── Fast, legacy hash used for fingerprints
│   │
│   ├── SHA-1
│   │   └── Deprecated hash with known weaknesses
│   │
│   └── SHA-256
│       └── Secure hash used for fingerprints and verification
│
├── Message Authentication (Integrity + Authenticity)
│   │
│   ├── HMAC
│   │   └── Hash combined with a secret key to authenticate messages
│   │
│   └── Poly1305
│       └── High-speed authenticator used with stream ciphers
│
└── AEAD (Encryption + Authentication)
    │
    ├── AES-GCM
    │   └── AES encryption with built-in authentication
    │
    └── ChaCha20-Poly1305
        └── Stream cipher with integrated authentication
